I"Š<p>For people like me with multiple pythons installations and can never remember his current modules are installed, I added the simple script, <code>where-python</code>:</p>
<pre>
python -c "import $1; import os; print os.path.dirname($1.__file__)"
</pre>
<p>And hence:</p>
<pre>$ where-python django
/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.4/lib/python2.4/site-packages/django
</pre>

